post_text:
Community Activities For Our Students

Our students are on Spring break this week but learning activities are still available to them. Check out Ms. Sherry Jameau's Story Hour below:

Hi, my name is Mz. Sherry. I live in Olympia Fields but work at Homewood Public Library. I would like to invite your children to Storyhour on Zoom. Reading stories helps to bring joy to young readers. They will hear stories, sing songs and and participate in other activities. When? Thursdays evenings at 5:30pm. Zoom meeting ID: 708-369-1915 Password: 9201. I hope that you will join me. Thank you

post_text:
Elementary School District 159 Presents: Understanding Federal Laws that May Efffect You and Your Family

Thursday, Jan. 16th from 6pm-8pm
Marya Yates Elementary School
6131 Allemong Dr. Matteson, IL 60443

Session 1: 6:00 PM to 6:55 PM
Session 2: 7:00 PM to 7:55 PM

post_text:
In Elementary School District 159 we work in partnership for the betterment of our youth.
Our partners FYI (Family Youth Initiative) provides an array of programs and services to our youth. Members of our team also includes Richton Park and Matteson Police Departments, social service agencies, and business owners.
Today we held our annual holiday luncheon and raffle to support our programs. Next month our youth are going skiing at no cost.

In the pictures are Police Chiefs White (Richton Park) and Jones (Matteson), School Dist,rict Superintendent Dr. Alfred, FYI Director/SD227 Board Member Mia Carter, Asst. Superintendent Dr. Johnson, District Public Relations Shelia Friday, and Matteson Village Manager, Anthony Burton
#WeAreESD159 #WatchUsSoar.

Second picture: FYI Member and business owner Angela Angela Sunshine Brummel, Dr. Johnson, Superintendent Alfred, and Community activist Mr Tony Bass.

post_text: Family Literacy Night gave our Colin Powell Middle School students an opportunity to learn about bats. Did you know that there are over 100 different bat species? These flying mammals can live over 20 years. Most bats feed on insects. However 3 bat species feed solely on blood by piercing an animals skin without them even noticing. Also, while others glide, bats are also the only mammals capable of continued flight. #WeAreESD159 #WatchUsSoar

post_text: Our school district started 150 years ago as a two-room school house named Sieden Prairie. Today we have four elementary schools and one middle school. As we honor our past, we also embrace our future. We are appreciative of our alumni, former administrators and staff, and board members, for your contribution to our school district. We will continue to strive to make our community proud. #WatchUsSoar

post_text:
Last night we recognized our SOARs (Superintendent Outstanding Achievement Recipient). Each of them were nominated by their principals for the extraordinary efforts they make in supporting our mission "To Educate, Empower and Inspire the Whole-child". Below are pictures of four of the six recipients and their principals: Sieden Prairie teacher Adrienne Smith and her principal Mrs. McCaskill, Neil Armstrong social worker Mr. Jabari Dowdell and principal Mrs. Etherly, Woodgate speech pathologist Rose Raebig and principal Dr. Hill, and Colin Powell teacher Kristin Mathews and principal Mr. Payne. Not shown in the pictures are two 3rd grade teachers from Marya Yates, Ms. Brianna Martin and Ms. Nakia Norman who also enjoyed the festivities. Congratulations and keep SOARing!
#WeAreESD159 #WatchUsSoar!

shared_text:
Elementary School District 159 Community
November 10, 2019 at 2:18 PM ·

Too often we take for granted how fortunate we are. Among other things, we're very fortunate to have been born in this country, which gives us opportunities and freedoms that people in other countries do not have the privilege of enjoying. Memorial Day and Veterans Day serve as reminders and is only ours because of the many brave people who give of and have given their lives to defend our country.

On behalf of the Board of Education and Superintendent of Elementary School District 159, we would like to honor all those who made the ultimate sacrifice by celebrating them, appreciating our freedoms and esteeming all Veterans and active military personnel. We salute you and give great recognition to all you have done.
Happy Veterans Day!
